ed to the options available in the table.","position":{"start":{"line":113,"column":1,"offset":5339},"end":{"line":113,"column":188,"offset":5526}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":113,"column":1,"offset":5339},"end":{"line":113,"column":188,"offset":5526}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Precise control with calc()","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":4,"offset":5531},"end":{"line":115,"column":31,"offset":5558}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1,"offset":5528},"end":{"line":115,"column":31,"offset":5558}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In his 2012 article on ","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1,"offset":5560},"end":{"line":117,"column":24,"offset":5583}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://trentwalton.com/2012/06/19/fluid-type/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Fluid Type","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":25,"offset":5584},"end":{"line":117,"column":35,"offset":5594}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":24,"offset":5583},"end":{"line":117,"column":83,"offset":5642}}},{"type":"text","value":" Trent Walton said:","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":83,"offset":5642},"end":{"line":117,"column":102,"offset":5661}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1,"offset":5560},"end":{"line":117,"column":102,"offset":5661}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"raw","value":"<blockquote>\"It's been hard to let go of setting a static font-size for a site and calling things done. I’m realizing that the predictability & control we've had over web type is becoming a thing of the past.\"</blockquote>","position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1,"offset":5663},"end":{"line":119,"column":223,"offset":5885}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"But perhaps not all predictability and control is lost.","position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1,"offset":5887},"end":{"line":121,"column":56,"offset":5942}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1,"offset":5887},"end":{"line":121,"column":56,"offset":5942}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Let's imagine that as a typography nerd with an eye for absolute precision, you want the font-size at a resolution of 600px to be 12px. Great! Looking at the table, setting a font-size of 2vw will achieve this. But you also want the font-size at 800px to be 32px. It seems you can’t do this without changing from 2vw to 4vw and this means a break-point and our font scaling will be jumpy and not fluid. I consider this a pretty significant limitation.","position":{"start":{"line":123,"column":1,"offset":5944},"end":{"line":123,"column":452,"offset":6395}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":123,"column":1,"offset":5944},"end":{"line":123,"column":452,"offset":6395}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"There is a solution to this! It's not exactly pretty but it works – at least in modern browsers. As stated earlier, some browser have bugs when using calc() and viewport units together, so this might be buggy in some older browsers. (This is not really a concern anymore, just set sensible default font sizes before declaring a fluid type calc() expression.)","position":{"start":{"line":125,"column":1,"offset":6397},"end":{"line":125,"column":359,"offset":6755}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":125,"column":1,"offset":6397},"end":{"line":125,"column":359,"offset":6755}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It appears that by using calc() and vw we can get responsive typography that scales perfectly between specific pixel values within a specific viewport range.","position":{"start":{"line":127,"column":1,"offset":6757},"end":{"line":127,"column":158,"offset":6914}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":127,"column":1,"offset":6757},"end":{"line":127,"column":158,"offset":6914}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This means you can have perfect smooth scaling between any 2 font sizes over any viewport range. The font will start scaling and stop scaling exactly where you want.","position":{"start":{"line":129,"column":1,"offset":6916},"end":{"line":129,"column":166,"offset":7081}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":129,"column":1,"offset":6916},"end":{"line":129,"column":166,"offset":7081}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Try the demo: ","position":{"start":{"line":131,"column":1,"offset":7083},"end":{"line":131,"column":15,"offset":7097}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://codepen.io/MadeByMike/pen/YPJJYv?editors=110"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Precise control over responsive typography","position":{"start":{"line":131,"column":16,"offset":7098},"end":{"line":131,"column":58,"offset":7140}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":131,"column":15,"offset":7097},"end":{"line":131,"column":112,"offset":7194}}},{"type":"text","value":"\nThe demo uses SASS so you can easily change the upper and lower limits of the font-size and media queries. But the important part looks something like this:","position":{"start":{"line":131,"column":112,"offset":7194},"end":{"line":132,"column":157,"offset":7351}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":131,"column":1,"offset":7083},"end":{"line":132,"column":157,"offset":7351}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"raw","value":"<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\">  <span class=\"token property\">font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token functio